@page "/"
@inject RubricCatalogStore Store

<PageTitle>CAI — the Codebase Assurance Index</PageTitle>

<HeadContent>
    <script type="application/ld+json">@((MarkupString)_glossaryJsonLd)</script>
</HeadContent>

<div class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">The open standard</p>
    <h1>An open, reproducible 0–100 standard for the health of a codebase.</h1>
    <p class="lede"><strong>Same code in, same score out</strong> — a measurement anyone can verify. The standard is
        composed of <strong>@_dimCount dimensions</strong> across <strong>@_lensCount lenses</strong>, each pinned to a
        versioned rubric. The method is open; the independent, signed survey is a service.</p>
    <div class="btns">
        <a class="btn primary" href="/spec">Read the spec</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/dimensions">Browse the @_dimCount dimensions</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/calculator">Score an evidence bundle →</a>
    </div>
</div></div>

<section><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Open · Verifiable · Referenced</h2>
    <div class="trio">
        <div class="card"><h3>Open</h3><p>The full catalog — @_dimCount dimensions, @_lensCount lenses — and the fold
            are public and versioned. A reference scorer ships under Apache-2.0.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Verifiable</h3><p>The score is deterministic. Same evidence + same rubric version ⇒ the
            same number — and you can <a href="/calculator">run it yourself</a>.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Referenced</h3><p>This site is the authority: the rubric catalogs are served by
            <a href="/api/rubrics">API</a>, so a survey, a contract, or a badge points back to a checkable record.</p></div>
    </div>
    <h3>The bands</h3>
    <div class="bands">
        <span class="band b-exemplary">Exemplary 90–100</span>
        <span class="band b-strong">Strong 70–89</span>
        <span class="band b-adequate">Adequate 50–69</span>
        <span class="band b-weak">Weak 25–49</span>
        <span class="band b-critical">Critical 0–24</span>
    </div>
</div></section>

<section><div class="wrap">
    <h2>The firewall — what is open, and what is judgment</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="font-size:1.05rem">The score, the findings, and the algorithm are the open standard:
        deterministic and reproducible. The surveyor's deductions and advice sit <em>outside</em> the firewall and never
        move the number. That boundary is also the free/paid line.</p>
    <figure class="fig">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 760 240" role="img" aria-label="The deterministic measurement is the open standard; advisory findings sit outside the firewall and never score.">
            <path class="ff-firewall" d="M610 28 v184" />
            <text class="ff-t" x="300" y="22" text-anchor="middle">The open standard — deterministic</text>
            <text class="ff-tm" x="300" y="226" text-anchor="middle">same evidence + same rubric version → the same number, reproducible by anyone</text>

            <rect class="ff-box" x="50" y="40" width="500" height="34" rx="6" />
            <text class="ff-t" x="300" y="62" text-anchor="middle">CAI 0–100 — the headline (never moves)</text>

            <rect class="ff-box" x="50" y="86" width="500" height="24" rx="5" />
            <text class="ff-t" x="300" y="103" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13">↑ worst-first ordered-weighted fold of the lenses</text>

            <g transform="translate(95, 140)">
                <circle class="ff-circle" cx="0" cy="0" r="11" />
                <circle class="ff-circle" cx="82" cy="0" r="11" />
                <circle class="ff-circle" cx="164" cy="0" r="11" />
                <circle class="ff-circle" cx="246" cy="0" r="11" />
                <circle class="ff-circle" cx="328" cy="0" r="11" />
                <circle class="ff-circle" cx="410" cy="0" r="11" />
            </g>
            <text class="ff-tm" x="300" y="182" text-anchor="middle">the lenses — each rolls up dimensions scored 0–10 by deterministic tools</text>

            <text class="ff-tm" x="685" y="22" text-anchor="middle">advisory</text>
            <rect class="ff-box-dim" x="640" y="40" width="90" height="130" rx="6" />
            <text class="ff-tm" x="685" y="96" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11">deductions</text>
            <text class="ff-tm" x="685" y="113" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11">&amp; advice</text>
            <text class="ff-tm" x="685" y="138" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11">(never</text>
            <text class="ff-tm" x="685" y="155" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11">scores)</text>
        </svg>
        <figcaption>Anyone can recompute the deterministic score from the open evidence; the advisory layer explains
            but never scores. Openness makes independence a fact you can check, not a claim.</figcaption>
    </figure>
</div></section>

<section><div class="wrap" style="text-align:center">
    <h2>The standard is free. The judgment is a service.</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="max-width:46rem;margin:0 auto 1.5rem">Use CAI to measure, compare, and verify any codebase
        yourself. When you need an independent, signed survey — the CAI plus the deductions and what to do about them —
        get one from the surveyor.</p>
    <a class="cta" href="https://watchdog.canine.dev">Get an independent survey →</a>
</div></section>

@code {
    private int _dimCount;
    private int _lensCount;
    private string _glossaryJsonLd = "";

    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        var c = Store.Get(Store.Latest() ?? "");
        _dimCount = c?.Dimensions.Count ?? 0;
        _lensCount = c?.Lenses.Count ?? 0;
        _glossaryJsonLd = Cai.Web.CaiGlossary.Build();
    }
}
